  "sourceType": "SYNTHESISED",
  "sourceNotes": "The tangzhong method (water roux or yudane) originates in Japanese and Taiwanese bakery tradition; it was popularised in English-language home baking by Yvonne Chen's Bread Doctor (2003) and subsequently adopted widely. The technique of gelatinising a portion of flour with liquid before mixing into the main dough increases water retention in the final bake, keeping the crumb soft without added preservatives.",
