  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termSlug": "tangzhong"
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "tangzhong"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is the step that distinguishes this from a standard enriched roll. When flour is cooked with liquid at around 65°C, the starch granules absorb and hold much more water than raw flour can. That extra held water remains in the crumb after baking, keeping the bun soft for two or three days without any additives."
          }
        ]
      },
